te\n!Number of votes\n!Share of votes\n!Outcome of election\n|-\n|[[1935 Philippine presidential election|1935]]\n|[[Sergio Osme\u00f1a]]\n|812,352\n|86.91%\n|Won\n|-\n|[[1941 Philippine presidential election|1941]]\n|[[Sergio Osme\u00f1a]]\n|1,445,897\n|92.10%\n|Won\n|-\n|[[1946 Philippine presidential election|1946]]\n|[[Eulogio Rodriguez]]\n|1,051,243\n|47.38%\n|Lost\n|-\n|[[1949 Philippine presidential election|1949]]\n|Manuel Briones\n|1,184,215\n|46.08%\n|Lost\n|-\n|[[1953 Philippine presidential election|1953]]\n|[[Carlos P. Garcia]]\n|2,515,265\n|62.90%\n|Won\n|-\n|[[1957 Philippine presidential election|1957]]\n|[[Jos\u00e9 Laurel Jr.]]\n|1,783,012\n|37.91%\n|Lost\n|-\n|[[1961 Philippine presidential election|1961]]\n|[[Gil Puyat]]\n|1,787,987\n|28.06%\n|Lost\n|-\n|[[1965 Philippine presidential election|1965]]\n|[[Fernando Lopez]]\n|3,531,550\n|48.48%\n|Won\n|-\n|[[1969 Philippine presidential election|1969]]\n|[[Fernando Lopez]]\n|5,001,737\n|62.76%\n|Won\n|-\n|[[1986 Philippine presidential election|1986]]\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|Supported [[Salvador Laurel]] who won\n|-\n|[[1992 Philippine presidential election|1992]]\n|[[Eva Estrada Kalaw]]\n|255,730\n|1.25%\n|Lost\n|-\n|[[1998 Philippine presidential election|1998]]\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|Did not take part\n|-\n|[[2004 Philippine presidential election|2004]]\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|Supported [[Noli de Castro]] who won\n|-\n|[[2010 Philippine presidential election|2010]]\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|Supported [[Loren Legarda]] who lost\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[2016 Philippine presidential election|2016]]\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|Supported either [[Alan Peter Cayetano]], [[Bongbong Marcos]] or [[Antonio Trillanes]] who all lost\n|}\n\n===Senate===\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Election\n!Number of votes\n!Share of votes\n!Seats won\n!Seats after\n!Outcome of election\n|-\n|[[1916 Philippine Senate elections|1916]]\n|\n|\n|See seats after\n|